description:
- Fits true to size.

Moth or marble? We can't decide which we love more. The third drop of Kenzo x New Era takes two more signature prints from Kenzo's Fall/Winter 2012 runway and throws them full-force at a set of six classic 59Fifty fitted caps. Grab them while you can! 

Fitted cap with embroidered Kenzo logo at back | Flat brim | Embroidered New Era flag at left side | 100% polyester | Made in China.

Designer

Kenzo

Passport: France

Established: 1970 by Kenzo Takada

With its famous "Jungle Jap" boutique at its center, Kenzo Takada's ready-to-wear empire captivated Paris and the world at large with its infectious energy. In 2011, OC's very own Carol Lim and Humberto Leon moved into Kenzo HQ on rue Vivienne to open a new chapter in the house's history. As creative directors, Carol and Humberto stay true to Kenzo's original triptych of bold prints, irresistible colors, and volume, while adding their own unique voice to the mix.

A playful take on fashion house Maison Martin Margiela‘s product numbering system, 40oz NYC‘s newest “Numbers” Snapback Caps altered the familiar 0 to 23 scheme with the addition of a circled “40″ at the end.
